Study_Purpose: Stormwater data is gathered to know possible pollutants from the Town of Coupeville.  The results of this study will be a part of the feasibility plan for a possible water reclamation project within the Town.
Ecology_Program_or_Other_Responsible_Ent: Ecy Water Quality Program, Northwest Region
Submitting_Organization: Island County Environmental Health - Coupeville WA
Study_QA_Project_Plan_Description: Five stormwater outfalls within the Town of Coupeville limits, draining into Penn Cove will be monitored once a month for the following parameters:  fecal coliform, ortho-phosphate, nitrate, pH, temperature, conductivity, dissolved oxygen and turbidity.  Sampling was done around the tide tables and storm events to ensure a sample could be taken if possible.
Study_QA_Assessment_Level: Level 4:  Data Verified and Assessed for Usability in a Formal Study Report
Study_Comment: Samples must be taken at periods of low tide
